<db:section xml:id="supportedApertures">
<db:title>QList&lt;qreal&gt; QCameraExposure::supportedApertures(bool *<db:emphasis>continuous</db:emphasis> = Q_NULLPTR) const</db:title>
<db:para>Returns the list of aperture values camera supports. The apertures list can change depending on the focal length, in such a case the <db:link xlink:href="qcameraexposure.xml#apertureRangeChanged">apertureRangeChanged</db:link>() signal is emitted.</db:para>
<db:para>If the camera supports arbitrary aperture values within the supported range, *<db:code role="parameter">continuous</db:code> is set to true, otherwise *<db:code role="parameter">continuous</db:code> is set to false.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="supportedIsoSensitivities">
<db:title>QList&lt;int&gt; QCameraExposure::supportedIsoSensitivities(bool *<db:emphasis>continuous</db:emphasis> = Q_NULLPTR) const</db:title>
<db:para>Returns the list of ISO senitivities camera supports.</db:para>
